 any person you choose. <p><IMG SRC = "http://laurenia.homestead.com/files/laurenia_sig_final.jpg" WIDTH=383 HEIGHT=223  BORDER=0><TABLE BORDER=0><TR><TD></A></TD></TR></TABLE><br><br><p align="center"><ahref="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/test3.htm"target="_blank"><imgsrc="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/mythresult/freshwaterseanymph.jpg"border="0" width="330" height="175"></a><br>I took the <ahref="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/test3.htm"target="_blank">What Mythological Creature Are you?</a> test by<lj user=peacefulchaos> !</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upeoni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peoni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/8/02 3:20:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wizard or necro?</span><hr size=1> Firstly, necromancers can root - they receive root at lvl 34<br><br>Benefits of a wizard in PvP<br>Higher damage nukes than any other class, throughout level advancement. No-one at low-mid levels can do the raw damage that a wizard is capable of (due to people having very low resistances at low level, your spells will often land for maximum damage - unless you're fighting twinks).<br>Nukes are effected by your targets resistances, until you receive lures (unresistable pvp nukes) at level 50+ - obviously quite some time away.<br>Gates and group ports, mean you're not stuck asking for lifts, and should you die, recovering your corpse on another continent isn't such an awkward task<br><br>Problems with a wizard in pvp ?<br>100% reliant on their mana to do damage from nukes - when your OOM, you're helpless.<br>No ability to self heal - you have to rely on your rune buffs and friendly priests.<br><br>Benefits of a Necro<br>Nukes (drains), may be lower in dealing damage and are alot less mana efficient than a wizard at dealing damage, but they heal at the same time as causing your opponent damage. Life taps/drains are also unresistable in PvP (a very big plus at higher levels when facing opponents with good resists).<br>Necros recieve many lines of DoT's that are also unresistable - this should be your main source of damage, using taps to heal yourself and finish an opponent who is at low life.<br>Pets - you recieve strong pets, who are able to do mana free damage once summoned - another benefit of a pet is that they can interupt casters from casting spells back, and they are also great at preventing melee's from using any non-instant item in pvp (pure melee's have no channelling skill). Having a pet also means you're not completely helpess when you're oom.<br><br>Problems with necro ?<br>Pets can be easily nullified - charm spells poof pets, snare/root are rarely resisted and easily keep a pet out of action if your opponent is clever.<br>You're life taps don't inflict massive damage in the way wizard nukes do - but then again you have more options open to you in pvp.<br>Obviously, you don't get any port spells, just the basic caster gate.<br><br> <p><b></FONT><FONT SIZE = "2" COLOR = "GREEN"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6917>Peoni Greenleaf </a>   <ahref=http://www.defiantvz.com>~Defiant~</a> <BR>Naturewalker of Tunare <BR>Vallon Zek<BR></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showPrevMessage?topicID=44.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showNextMessage?topicID=44.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?t